Lambert (closure inversion)

WвҖ“Lambert is the inversion step when the model tries to compress/close its state update into a stable representation (self-reference).

Branch behavior corresponds to discrete вҖңmode switchesвҖқ (different internal regimes).

Jump (rebasing the representation)

A jump corresponds to the system deciding:

вҖңI cannot continue refining in the same basis; I must represent the next window in a new coordinate frame.вҖқ

That is: update the representation basis for the next context window.

So: WвҖ“Lambert loops are not вҖңtokensвҖқ; they are the internal closure dynamics of how a model compresses the present into the next state. Kakeya is the global uncertainty pressure that forces or prevents rebasing.

